"Clear," you shout back to your squadmates.\n\nDelta, Gamma, and Epsilon cautiously walk into the corridor, surveying the cleanliness of the whole scene. Delta brushes by you as she looks for anything resembling controls for the far hatchway. Gamma peers into the deserted control room. \n\n"You okay?" Epsilon's voice catches you by surprise. The voice apparently shook you more than you realized. \n\n[[No. I heard...something.|Open the Hatch][$groupConcern += 1]]\n[[Yeah. This is just...odd.|Open the Hatch]]
You listen silently to what the voice is saying, hoping to find a pattern or any other clue as to what it's trying to tell you. Even with your attempts to hear it, the voice quickly fades away, leaving you to wonder what it could mean. \n\n"Report." Gamma's order breaks you out of your trance.\n"No one here. We need to get the station hatch open from this side," you reply. \n"On it." Delta comes through the dropship hatch and begins searching for anything resembling door controls. Gamma and Epsilon follow a few moments later surveying the corridor as they do. \n\nGamma walks over to the window into the control room while Epsilon approaches you. \n\n[["You notice anything odd?" you ask her.|Open the Hatch]]
As Epsilon pulls the hatch open, you ready your laser rifle and proceed into the airlock between the station and the dropship. An eerily clean, white corridor greets you as you step out of the red light. No one is there to greet you. You peer into the airlock's control room. Empty. As you survey the corridor further, you think you hear [[something.|First Obelisk Encounter]]

The main cabin of the dropship pulses softly with red light, accenting the dull grey bulkheads with hard shadows cast by you and your squadmates every few seconds. Every so often, one of them would turn perfectly to project a red spotlight in the direction they were looking. The cabin is just barely big enough for four heavily armored soldiers to move comfortably without bumping into each other. Cables snake along the walls and ceiling from the cockpit to the rear hatch where you and Epsilon stand on either side. \n\n"Everyone clear?" Gamma says as he walks over to Epsilon. \n"Figure out why the station's dark and if anyone is still alive" Epsilon replies.\n\nDelta walks behind you and mirrors Gamma's position behind you. She puts a gauntleted hand on your shoulder.\n\n"First time for everything, eh?" \n"I can't imagine what you're talking about" you reply.\n"Deneb. You've never been." \n"Oh, //that//."\n\nDelta playfully taps the back of your helmet and is interrupted by the pilot announcing that we will dock in 30 seconds. Silence overtakes the cabin as everyone waits those 30 excruciating seconds. Finally the sound of metal on metal pierces the silence and the dropship rocks uneasily as the pilot fights to align the dropship's hatch with the station's. \n\n"No one's home," Delta muses. \n"Or at least no one's available," Epsilon adds. \n"Cut it," Gamma interjects, returning the uneasy silence to you and your squadmates. \n\nAnother jolt and metalic screech as the pilot continues the attempt to dock. Finally she lets you know that the dropship has indeed docked with the station. Gamma motions for Epsilon to open the hatch and for you to be ready to enter [[the breach.|Entrance]]
You take point as the squad inches its way down the sterile corridor. The lights flicker for another minute then go out. You tap a button on your forearm and a beam of light erupts from your helmet, followed by three others from your squadmates. \n\n"Why would the power go out?" Delta asks. "There's no signs of combat, everyone's just...gone." \n"Anyone know what they were researching here?" Epsilon adds.\n"Classified," Gamma replies. \n"You don't have access?" you inquire. \n"Not to a blackops station," comes the curt response. \n\nAs you continue down the corridor, out of the corner of your eye, you see a shadow, not your own, and not of your squadmates'. You pause to inspect it. Shining your flashlight on it doesn't change the shadow's intensity or position, though it does react in what could be interpreted as annoyance. \n\n"Find something?" Gamma asks. \n"Something...or someone, I'm not sure," you reply. \n\nGamma walks over to where you are shining your light. The shadow backs slightly further down the corridor. Epsilon and Delta shine their lights in the shadow's direction, causing it to scitter into the darkness. Gamma spins around to face Delta and Epsilon. \n\n"Delta, get as many explosives as you can from the dropship."\n"What's going on?" Delta asks nervously.\n"No time," he replies and turns to face you. "You and Epsilon figure out what they were researching here." \n\nHe takes off running down the corridor towards the air lock with Delta trailing behind. \n\n<<if $groupConcern == 1>>"You think that's what you heard?" Epsilon asks.\n"Could be. Was this what Gamma was worried about?" \n"I don't think he knew what to be worried about, just that we were kept in the dark about what was going on here has him on edge," she replies.\n<<else if $corruption == 1>>"Was this what you were referring to in the airlock?" Epsilon asks.\n"No..."\n<<else>>"You think this is why we only got static and not a distress call?" Epsilon asks.\n"Definitely could be. Might also have to do with why there are no bodies." \n"What, like a nuclear blast? Then why is the station intact?" she observes.\n"Fair point." \n<<endif>>\n[[Epsilon starts down the corridor<<if $corruption == 1>> appearing suspicious of your evasiveness. With your light barely illuminating Epsilon, the voice returns, this time a little clearer. You can at least understand a single word. "Stop." \n\n[["Stop what?"|Listen to Second Voice][$corruption += 1]]\n[[Ignore it. The station is getting to your head|Ignore Second Voice]]
When you step into the room, the light fades, revealing a massive, shining, black obelisk in the middle of the room. Light arcs across its surface, causing ripples and waves over the obsidian-like material. You take a few steps towards the obelisk. The light arcing across its surface intensifies slightly. You signal Epsilon to move further into the lab. As she does this, you move over to the obelisk and reach towards it.\n\n"What are you-" Epsilon exclaims as your gauntleted hand makes contact with the obelisk's surface. In spite of its liquid appearance, it is somehow completely solid. \n<<if $corruption == 2>>"Stop...her..." the voice thunders in your head. "Stop her."\n"Her?" you wheel around towards Epsilon. Through her helmet and visor you can tell she is in shock, though not enough to keep from training the laser rifle on your head. Silence hangs between the two of you. \n"I thought you were acting strange..." she muses, keeping the rifle trained on your head.\nYou notice the arm still holding the rifle slowly beginning to point it at her.\n"What?" you watch helplessly as the arm holding the rifle finally points directly at Epsilon's chest.\n\nYou and Epsilon stare at each other as she slowly circles you and backs towards the door. You focus all your energy on not pulling the trigger, but you feel your fingers edge closer with every breath. In the distance, you hear rapidly approaching footsteps. You remain focused on bending your rogue arm to your will as Epsilon edges back and forth in front of the door, weapon still trained on your head. Your arm slightly lags behind her movements. Finally, the footsteps are deafening. Gamma and Delta, loaded down with explosives, burst into the room, weapons ready. Your arm jerks in Gamma's direction and fires. The shot misses him and scars the corridor behind him with melting metal. Gamma fires back and a burning sensation erupts through your chest. You look down to see melting armor mixing with your blood trickling down to the floor around your feet. Your hand touching the obelisk slides off and you collapse onto the floor. The world around you grows dark. You think you see the shadow from before on the ceiling, but you're not sure. You can only just make out Gamma and Epsilon's voices over the faint sounds of Delta wiring explosives. The sounds cease and your vision fades into inky blackness. You feel something warm envelop your body, then, nothing...<<else if $groupConcern > 0>>The lights arcing across the obelisk glow brighter and the seeming turbulence on its surface intensifies. Epsilon rushes over and pulls you away from the obelisk. The light surrounding the obelisk intensifies and spreads outward. Epsilon drags you out of the lab, away from the expanding arcs. You spy one of the arcs contact a table, causing it to vanish, leaving only its shadow to remain. You hear faint echoes of footsteps closing in as Epsilon drags you to the door.\n\n"I think I know what that voice you heard was," she shouts as she tries unsuccessfully to shut the door to the lab.\n"You mean that thing?" you feebly answer.\n"Yeah. I think it's why we didn't see any bodies," she adds as she drags you further away from the lab. The footsteps are almost on top of you now.\n"And the shadow? You saw what happened to the table right?" Your voice is ragged. \n"Your guess is as good as any," she answers as Gamma and Delta reach you.\n"Status?" Gamma is curt as ever.\n"No time," you manage and point down the corridor where an arc of light has crossed the threshold.\n"Grenades?" Epsilon asks.\n\nDelta produces a belt of ten and motions for Epsilon to get you back to the dropship. As Epsilon hoists you into a better position to carry you, an explosion rocks the corridor and you watch as debris explodes out of the lab into the corridor. Epsilon takes off as fast as she can carrying you. Through the smoke you catch sight of Gamma and Delta sprinting towards you. As Epsilon reaches the airlock, you catch a last glimpse of the shadow seemingly nodding a "thank you" then vanishing. Epsilon sets you down on the hard, metalic deck of the dropship as Gamma and Delta charge through the hatchway. Epsilon slams the hatchway shut and the dropship shudders as the combine forces of the explosion and its own thrusters toss it about. The dropship finally rights itself and you stand up to see through the small window on the hatch. You can't find any trace of the station or the obelisk, but that could be from shock...<<else>>The lights arcing across the obelisk's surface brighten at your touch, causing the surface to further distort. You turn to see Epsilon slowly raising her rifle in your direction. Footsteps faintly echo in the corridor behind her.\n\n"What are you doing?" She suspiciously eyes you.\nYou take a step towards her, causing your hand to slip off the obelisk and her weapon to train itself on your head. \n"Calm down. Curiosity...just got the better of me." Your voice is slightly panicked at both your actions and hers.\n\nYou notice her ease up on her weapon and stare past you at the obelisk. You turn to see the arcs grow dimmer and deeper into its structure. The footsteps grow closer and Gamma and Delta finally appear at the lab door's threshold, their lights still on. When beams from their lights connect with the obelisk, the beams wrap around it, turning into more arcs encircling the artifact. Gamma and Delta immediately switch off their lights, though the obelisk remains in its slightly more luminous state.\n\n"What the hell is that?" Delta asks as she begins placing charges.\n"Probably the source of the shadow," Gamma replies as he rigs a timer.\n\nYou and Epsilon help the others finish wiring the explosives and turn to leave. Gamma sets the timer for 90 seconds and begins the countdown. At the start of the countdown, the obelisk comes to life. The arcs of light return to its surface and begin expanding outward. Gamma hurredly sets the timer for 45 seconds as Epsilon tries to drag him out of the lab and away from the light arcs. You and Delta are already in the corridor as the other two tumble out, pick themselves up, and sprint towards the dropship. As you reach the airlock, the station shudders and you and your squadmates scramble into the dropship's cabin. Before you slam the hatch shut, you make out the shadow motioning some sort of "farewell" to you as it vanishes and debris fills the void. You slam the hatch shut as the dropship struggles to break free of the collapsing station. The sounds of metal on metal finally cease as the dropship tumbles away from the station. Once the pilot regains control, you manage to see the molten slag of the station vanish into oblivion as the arcs of light disperse into the void. Nothing but memories remain...<<endif>>
After the unification of Earth, humanity has spread across the stars, finding little outside of new places to call home.\n\nFew of those responsible for humanity's unity remain and lay forgotten to all but themselves. These few still protect humanty from the shadows, though even they are showing signs of wear, for centuries will take their toll on everyone. \n\nRumors have surfaced of the discovery of ancient artifacts in the remote Deneb system. You catch up with Epsilon further down the corridor where she is fiddling with a lock on a door labeled "Medical Section."\n\n<<if $groupConcern > 0>>"You okay back there? Took you a while," she notes.\n"I heard the voice again," you nervously answer.\n"Did it say anything?"\n"All I could make out was 'stop.' You think this has to do with Gamma ordering us to destroy this place?"\n"You're hearing voices, there's a shadow without a person, the station is completely sterile, so yes," she replies.\n"Does he know more than he's letting on?" you ask.\n"He's a pretty open book who's better read than most. If I were to say anything it's that he's a little paranoid." She punches the locking mechanism, ruining it further. "No good.
